<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="389" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,261,1548]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,333,360]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The salient features of the new species include the following: anal segment of male with lateroapical processes asymmetrical, left one distinctly longer than right one (
<figureCitation box="[880,963,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
); pygofer in posterior view with 4 spinous medioventral processes (
<figureCitation box="[428,512,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
); aedeagus with long spinous process at base, apex acute, directed ventrad, middle ventral margin of aedeagus without process (
<figureCitation box="[654,738,441,467]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
); apex of genital style not forked (
<figureCitation box="[1122,1253,441,467]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Figs 23, 24</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,261,1548]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,477,504]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Coloration.</emphasis>
General color yellowish brown with green. Frons, vertex, pronotum and mesonotum with median carina white bordered with blackish brown (
<figureCitation box="[642,773,513,540]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Figs 15–17</figureCitation>
). Eyes dark brown to blackish brown; ocelli reddish brown. Antennae with dorsal and ventral margins and apex of scape, base and near apex of pedicel dark brown to blackish brown (
<figureCitation box="[239,323,585,612]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Lateral margins of frons, gena, vertex and pronotum each with oblique white band bordered with brown or dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[404,534,621,648]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Figs 15, 16</figureCitation>
). Cypeus yellowish white (
<figureCitation box="[840,924,621,648]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Forewings with yellowish brown over basal third, rest area hyaline, along transverse vein and apical veins with brown stripes as figured (
<figureCitation box="[1199,1282,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
), in dark portion veins with white spots. Wings hyaline with brown veins. Legs yellowish brown. Abdomen with dorsum dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,261,1548]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,409,766,792]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Head and thorax.</emphasis>
Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[506,587,765,792]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) wider at base than long submedially about 1.55: 1. Frons longer in middle line than wide at widest part about 1.26: 1, widest just above ocelli.Antennae surpassing frontoclypeal suture, scape long equal to wide, shorter than pedicel about 0.38: 1 (
<figureCitation box="[777,862,837,864]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Pronotum shorter than vertex about 0.70: 1. Mesonotum longer in middle line than vertex and pronotum combined about 1.84: 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1065,1148,873,900]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Forewing in middle line longer than wide at widest part about 2.34: 1 (
<figureCitation box="[667,750,909,935]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,261,1548]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,375,945,972]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Anal segment of male short, lateroapical angles produced into stout spinous process respectively, asymmetric, left one distinctly longer than right one (
<figureCitation box="[774,857,981,1007]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). Pygofer in posterior view ventral margin with four medioventral processes, finger-like (
<figureCitation box="[560,642,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), in lateral view ventral angles distinctly produced (
<figureCitation box="[1224,1308,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[160,240,1053,1079]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) with long spinous process at base, S-shaped curved, apex acute, directed ventrad. Genital styles divergent, long, reaching ventral margin of anal segment, broad at base, narrowing to apex (
