<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="389" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,261,1548]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1198,1224]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ding, 1990" authorityName="Ding" authorityYear="1990" box="[607,926,1197,1224]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Arcofacies" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigatipennis">
<emphasis box="[607,792,1198,1224]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">A. strigatipennis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ding, J. - H." box="[800,926,1197,1223]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389" pagination="74 - 77" refId="ref4138" refString="Ding, J. - H. (1990) Notes on the genus Arcofacies in China (Homoptera: Delphacidae). Journal of Bamboo Research, 9 (1), 74 - 77." type="journal article" year="1990">Ding, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but differs by: (1) anal segment of male with lateroapical processes asymmetrical, left one distinctly longer than right one (
<figureCitation box="[1015,1096,1233,1259]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) (anal segment with lateroapical processes symmetrical in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ding" authorityYear="1990" box="[475,659,1270,1296]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Arcofacies" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigatipennis">
<emphasis box="[475,659,1270,1296]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">A. strigatipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (2) pygofer in posterior view with 4 spinous medioventral processes (
<figureCitation box="[160,244,1305,1331]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) (pygofer in posterior view without medioventral process in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ding" authorityYear="1990" box="[955,1144,1306,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Arcofacies" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigatipennis">
<emphasis box="[955,1144,1306,1332]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">A. strigatipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (3) aedeagus with long spinous process at base, middle ventral margin without process (
<figureCitation box="[876,958,1341,1367]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1731,1756]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,187,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1414,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Arcofacies varius sp. nov. 13. Male habitus, dorsal view; 14. Same, lateral view; 15. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 16. Face; 17. Frons, lateral view; 18. Forewing; 19. Male genitalia, ventral view; 20. Same, lateral view; 21.Anal segment, right lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, left lateral view; 23. Genital style, ventral view; 24. Same, left lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (13, 14, 18); 0.2 mm (15–17, 19–24)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3567322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3567322/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) (aedeagus broad at base, nearly quadrate, middle of dorsal margin and ventral margin each with process in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ding" authorityYear="1990" box="[880,1065,1378,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Arcofacies" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigatipennis">
<emphasis box="[880,1065,1378,1404]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">A. strigatipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="389" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,261,1548]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1414,1440]" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin word “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li &amp; Yang &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2019" box="[914,984,1414,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Arcofacies" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varius">
<emphasis box="[914,984,1414,1439]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="389">varius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (meaning different, changeable), referring to the anal segment with two asymmetrical processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
